spanGrp.span: n de tɔ́gɔ le Sánba Tɛ́ɛdunɔ
n de n bɔ́ɔ-den Dɔ̀gɔmɛ yan hɔ́ɗɛ̀ tɔ le
I come from this village, from Dogomet.
n bɔ́ɔ-ta ɲɔ́ɔ le, n nàata Dɔ̀gɔmɛ yan nɛ́tɔ
I left there and I came here, to Dogomet
háa kɛ́ɛ la bón kóè bòyita
Till the problem of this house (of the rural radio) was raised
an kó, ma i tɛ́stɛ kɛ́ɛ
He told that we should make a test
ɓá ma bá tɛ́stu kɛ́ɛ, n ka tɛ́stu sɔ̀tɔ, ma tága-ta Máamun, ma ka fɔ́rmasyɔn kɛ́ɛ ɲɔ́ɔ
When we made the test, we went to Mamu and we had a training there
n nàata Dɔ̀gɔmɛ yan nɛ́tɔ, n de le bi ɛɛ.. màsíɲɛ̀nù fóo kùnma, n de le bi kɛ́ɛ-la sábu là
I came here to Dogeme, I'm in charge of all the equipment, I'm doing the mediation
mɔ̀gɛ́ɛ̀nù fóo ni rádyo kúlè mɔ́ɛ
so that everybody listens to the radio
The voice of radio is here
a bi tága-la háa súprɛfɛtir múgan nin kɔ̀nɔntɔ
an fóo.. anu bi kɛɛ rádyo kúlè mɔ́ɛ-la kóoben
they all listen to the radio
wo bɔ́ɔnden tɛ́knisyɛn-ya le bólè tɔ
si ɓá.. si i bátaa mɔ́ɛ rádyo kɛ kúlè díi
as you've heard that the voice of the radio is good
it's that the technician accepted, (it's due to the technician)
ɓá saa gbɛ́ɛ-ta tún, rádyo kúlè si gbɛ́ɛ
Because if it's good, the sound of the radio is good
saa máa gbɛ́ɛ, a tée bɛ̀n
if it's not good, it doesn't work
wo yan káa, n de le bi zúrnalisunù fóo málɔ̀ɔ-la
now, it's me who accompanies all the journalists
ɛ́misyɔnnù tàa dúla n de le bi tága-la anu fɛ
I go with them to make a broadcast.
mɔ̀gɛ́ɛ̀nù si káwandili kɛ́ɛ kómin nà
n de le baanu ma-dɛ̀ɛman-na, háa an ni wo ɲɔ́ɔ fóo tàa
I help them so that they can make it all
bìi a... si ma bɔ́ɔ-ta ɲɔ́ɔ, mɔ̀gɛ́ɛ̀nù dóonù bi ɲɔ́ɔ, fúla mùséènù
When we leave there.. there are some men, Fulbe women
si wo máa màninká mùséènù, si wo máa álmaamiyaka-nù
if it's not Maninka women, if it's not Kakabe people,
an i.. an i sígè láa, an na kúlè tɔ
they sing songs in their language
ɛɛ.. ma le la rádyo búutɛ̀ tɔ yan nɛ́tɔ
kákkabɛ kúlè ɛɛ... sánsɔn bi yan nɛ́tɔ
a sígè.. a sígè, a tɔ́gɔ le kó sígè
an na sígè bi yan kóoben
There are a lot of songs
an.. an baa fɔ́ɔ-la mín nà, kó ístwar dɛ wílaz.. wo tɔ́gɔ káma le hɔ́ɗɔ táariku
When they sart to tell village stories
hɔ́ɗɔ táariku wo i mùn ma, mínnù prɛ́ dònta hɔ́ɗɛ̀ wo tɔ
this village story it's about those who were the first inhabitans of the village
wo le tɔ́gɔ le kó hɔ́ɗɛ̀ táariku
This is what is called village story
n de le bi kɛ́ɛ-la wo sábu là, háa ma naa ma-sɔ̀tɔ kóoben, ma naa la-gbɛ́ɛ kóoben, ma naa la-tànbi jàmáà ma
I'm the who is the assistant for this so that we register it, that we do it properly, that be pass it to people
so that they hear well the sound
si n kée-ta ɲɔ́ɔ, n si dán ɲɔ́ɔ
Since I've arrive here, I want to stop here
n de tɔ́gɔ le Sánta Tɛ́ɛdunɔ
